ZCZC GE68
EXTENDED OUTLOOK
SUNDAY TO WEDNESDAY
ISSUED BY THE MET OFFICE ON BEHALF OF THE MARITIME AND COASTGUARD AGENCY
AT 102300 UTC
HIGH PRESSURE 1021 LIES OVER SCOTLAND SUNDAY EVENING WITH LOW PRESSURE
1001 OVER CENTRAL SWEDEN LEADING TO A TIGHTENING PRESSURE PATTERN. ON MONDAY
THE HIGH DRIFTS E TO DOMINATE THE N SEA 1022 BEFORE MOV FURTHER E AND EXPANDING
ACROSS THE NORWEGIAN BASIN AND WERN BALTIC INTO TUESDAY AND WEDNESDAY. THIS
DEEP AREA OF LOW PRESSURE IN THE N ATLANTIC 970 TO START MOVS E TO BECOME
CENTRED CLOSE TO ICELAND SLWY FLN. MEANWHILE A SHALLOW AREA OF LOW PRESSURE
LOOKS TO DEVELOPS ALONG THE ENGLISH CHANNEL AND PUSH SLWY N AND E INTO THE
SERN N SEA WITH A FURTHER RIDGE OF HIGH PRESSURE LOOKING TO BUILD BEHIND
IT INTO THE FAR SW OF THE REGION BY THE END OF THE PERIOD. CONFIDENCE BECOMES
LOW BY THIS STAGE HOWEVER. LATE SUNDAY THERE IS A RISK OF NEAR GALE FORCE
WINDS FOR THE EERN N SEA WITH THIS RISK REDUCING INTO MONDAY
